The paper deals with information theory and communication, specifically the successive refinement problem with receiver side information. This falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of common randomness and binning, which are common techniques in source coding (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the joint distribution of the source and side information, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.MM) and the characterization of the admissible rate region, which is related to learning theory (cs.LG).
